page.title: 01Douglas Valley Walk I
page.content: A little while back on the 4th. July, six children out of our class (Fairlie School, Skelmersdale) went for a walk along the canal at Parbold. We started off from a new bridge. It was near an animal feed factory. We walked for abot 2 minutes and came across a barge painted up. We noticed a few dead fish. We came to a bridge with a number which was 38. We walked past some houses that backed on to the canal. Soon we passed a person fishing and came to another bridge _ this time number 39. The next bridge was number 40, and above the canal to the north was the railway and to the south the River Douglas.
